		<title>Top Books of 2014</title>
		<link>http://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/2014/12/top-books-2014.html</link>
		<comments>http://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/2014/12/top-books-2014.html#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Wed, 10 Dec 2014 11:00:45 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[K.M. Weiland &#124; @KMWeiland]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Writing Life]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[reading]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[writing life]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/?p=7860</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<p>Every year, I find myself reading with the maniac intensity of someone who believes it might be the last reading year. (I like to turn everything into an extreme sport.) After all, what self-respecting writer doesn&#8217;t study at the feet of the masters as much as she can? I had so much fun sharing my [&#8230;]</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/2014/12/top-books-2014.html">Top Books of 2014</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com">Helping Writers Become Authors</a>.</p>
]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Every year, I find myself reading with the maniac intensity of someone who believes it might be the last reading year. (I like to turn everything into an extreme sport.) After all, what self-respecting writer doesn&#8217;t study at the feet of the masters as much as she can? I had so much fun sharing <a title="Top Books of 2013" href="http://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/2013/12/top-20-books-2013.html" target="_blank">my top books from last year</a> that I couldn&#8217;t wait to do it again. So, without further ado, here are my top books of 2014.</p>
<p>I try to read three or four books at a time: a novel, a general non-fiction book, a writing book, and a devotional book. Below, you can find my Top 5 favorites in each category.</p>
<p>But, first, here are my stats for the year:</p>
<p><b>Total books read:</b> 135</p>
<p><b>Fiction to non-fiction ratio: </b>61:74</p>
<p><b>Male to female author ratio: </b>81:54</p>
<p><b>Top 5 genres: </b>Non-Fiction History (with 36 books), Classic Fiction (with 25), Writing How-To (with 15), Fantasy (with 11), and Historical Fiction (with 9).</p>
<p><b>Number of books per rating: </b>5 stars (6), 4 stars (48), 3 stars (53), 2 stars (21), 1 star (4).</p>
<h2>Top Fiction Books</h2>
<div id="attachment_8003" style="width: 209px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0099908603/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=0099908603&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=httpwwwkmweil-20&amp;linkId=UAILAPVVZY7T23WK" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img class="wp-image-8003 size-medium" src="http://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/For-Whom-the-Bell-Tolls-Ernest-Hemingway-199x300.jpg" alt="For Whom the Bell Tolls Ernest Hemingway" width="199" height="300" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text"><strong>1.</strong> <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0099908603/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=0099908603&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=httpwwwkmweil-20&amp;linkId=UAILAPVVZY7T23WK" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><em>For Whom the Bell Tolls</em></a> by Ernest Hemingway</p></div>
<div id="attachment_8004" style="width: 209px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00OOZP8JA/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B00OOZP8JA&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=httpwwwkmweil-20&amp;linkId=3LB2TFOXDEMVQS6X" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img class="wp-image-8004 " src="http://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/The-Officer’s-Code-by-Lyn-Alexander.jpg" alt=" The Officer’s Code by Lyn Alexander" width="199" height="316" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text"><strong>2.</strong> <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00OOZP8JA/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B00OOZP8JA&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=httpwwwkmweil-20&amp;linkId=3LB2TFOXDEMVQS6X" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><em>The Officer’s Code</em></a> by Lyn Alexander</p></div>
<div id="attachment_8005" style="width: 204px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B0076DDFCO/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B0076DDFCO&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=httpwwwkmweil-20&amp;linkId=XGZGVWFEH4P72MOS" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img class="wp-image-8005 size-medium" src="http://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/The-Blinding-Knife-by-Brent-Weeks-194x300.jpg" alt="The Blinding Knife by Brent Weeks" width="194" height="300" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text"><strong>3.</strong> <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B0076DDFCO/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B0076DDFCO&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=httpwwwkmweil-20&amp;linkId=XGZGVWFEH4P72MOS" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><em>The Blinding Knife</em></a> by Brent Weeks</p></div>
<div id="attachment_8006" style="width: 205px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B005EU50HY/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B005EU50HY&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=httpwwwkmweil-20&amp;linkId=TBZUOFIYEV63EN5L" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img class="wp-image-8006 size-medium" src="http://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Rose-Garden-Susanna-Kearsley-195x300.jpg" alt=" Rose Garden Susanna Kearsley" width="195" height="300" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text"><strong>4.</strong>  <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B005EU50HY/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B005EU50HY&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=httpwwwkmweil-20&amp;linkId=TBZUOFIYEV63EN5L" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><em>The Rose Garden</em></a> by Susanna Kearsley</p></div>
<div id="attachment_8007" style="width: 204px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B004J4WKUQ/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B004J4WKUQ&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=httpwwwkmweil-20&amp;linkId=ZYLZQEMY6DZQOYPV" rel="nofollow"><img class="wp-image-8007 size-medium" src="http://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Ready-Player-One-Ernest-Cline-194x300.jpg" alt="Ready Player One Ernest Cline" width="194" height="300" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text"><strong>5.</strong> <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B004J4WKUQ/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B004J4WKUQ&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=httpwwwkmweil-20&amp;linkId=ZYLZQEMY6DZQOYPV" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><em>Ready Player One</em></a> by Ernest Cline</p></div>
<h2>Top General Non-Fiction Books</h2>
<div id="attachment_8008" style="width: 205px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0671793373/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=0671793373&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=httpwwwkmweil-20&amp;linkId=D3S6USDBBASJHQ5M" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img class="wp-image-8008 size-medium" src="http://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/What-Jane-Austen-Ate-and-Charles-Dickens-Knew-Daniel-Pool-195x300.jpg" alt="What Jane Austen Ate and Charles Dickens Knew by Daniel Pool" width="195" height="300" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text"><strong>1.</strong> <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0671793373/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=0671793373&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=httpwwwkmweil-20&amp;linkId=D3S6USDBBASJHQ5M" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><em>What Jane Austen Ate and Charles Dickens Knew</em></a> by Daniel Pool</p></div>
<div id="attachment_8009" style="width: 210px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B000LA1I3W/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B000LA1I3W&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=httpwwwkmweil-20&amp;linkId=O4H3RQR76FDOSQUF" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img class="wp-image-8009 " src="http://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/This-Fabulous-Century-1940-1950-Time-Life-232x300.jpg" alt="This Fabulous Century 1940-1950 Time Life" width="200" height="259" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text"><strong>2.</strong> <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B000LA1I3W/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B000LA1I3W&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=httpwwwkmweil-20&amp;linkId=O4H3RQR76FDOSQUF" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><em>This Fabulous Century: 1940-1950</em></a> by Time Life</p></div>
<div id="attachment_8010" style="width: 209px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/1568521103/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=1568521103&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=httpwwwkmweil-20&amp;linkId=XTR25KJ6EW4LZMQW" target="_blank"><img class="wp-image-8010 " src="http://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Soldiers-John-Keegan-Richard-Holmes.jpg" alt="Soldiers John Keegan Richard Holmes" width="199" height="247" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text"><strong>3.</strong> <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/1568521103/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=1568521103&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=httpwwwkmweil-20&amp;linkId=XTR25KJ6EW4LZMQW" target="_blank"><em>Soldiers</em></a> by John Keegan and Richard Holmes</p></div>
